# ---

# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
# description only.
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline —
# this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# CVE-2026-0286 — PAN-OS Authenticated Command Injection in CLI (Management Plane)
# The vulnerability exists in the PAN-OS management plane CLI, where improper
# input handling allows an authenticated administrator to inject OS commands.
# Management plane access is typically exposed over HTTPS (port 443) via the
# web UI or over SSH (port 22). This rule targets HTTPS management plane
# traffic carrying shell metacharacter sequences commonly associated with
# command injection payloads (e.g., semicolons, backticks, $() subshell
# syntax, pipe characters in URI/POST body contexts).
#
# NOTE: NVD scores this CVSS 7.2 HIGH [1]; the CNA record at CVE.org scores
# it CVSS v4.0 6.0 MEDIUM [3]. This discrepancy is unresolved — analyst
# review of the applicable scoring is required before prioritising this rule.
# The Palo Alto Networks advisory assigns MODERATE urgency and MEDIUM severity
# with UNREPORTED exploit maturity [2]. No CISA KEV listing is present in
# the provided context; is_kev is set to false.
#
# Because the vulnerability requires prior administrator authentication, this
# rule is best deployed at the management network perimeter where unauthenticated
# vs authenticated sessions can be distinguished by posture, not by the rule
# itself. False-positive rate may be elevated in environments with complex CLI
# automation; analyst tuning is strongly recommended before production deployment.
#
# THIS IS A PROPOSED DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW. Do not deploy without
# validation against your environment's PAN-OS management traffic baseline.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET 443 (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-0286 PAN-OS Management Plane Authenticated Command Injection Attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.uri; content:"/php/utils/"; nocase;
  pcre:"/[;&|`]|\$\(|\$\{|%3B|%7C|%60/i";
  reference:cve,2026-0286;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1059, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-admin; sid:9000286; rev:1; )

